## Introduction

Claw Command Officer (later CCO) is an specialized member of the Blueshield program tasked with protecting Command and Crew onboard the station. Alongside advising its crew and command in regards to SOP and safety.

## Their place in Chain of Command

The CCO answers directly to Central Command, however they are obliged to follow any resonable orders from NTR, Captain, Head of Personel and Head of Sercurity, it is also advised (not required) they follow any reasonable requests from department Heads and optionaly crew. Their requests being pioritipiorin acordance to Chain of Command with NTR having piority.

## Promoting and Demoting a CCO

COO answers directly to Central Command, however they may be demoted if a vote including all present departamental Heads (including NTR) is held and at least 75% of votes are supporting the decision. Votes of the captain and NTR count as 2. Central Command is to be informed via fax if such vote is held even if it does not result in a demotion. In situations of emergancy Captain with aproval of NTR, if one is present, may hold such vote via radio communication methods.

Crew is forbiden from electing an acting CCO without Central Command aproval. However if one is granted for a candidate they must be aditionaly aproved by 75% of votes (Captains and NTRs vote count as 2) during an in person vote.

## CCOs responsibilities and requirements:

- CCO is permited to carry lethal munition and longarms at all times, however longarms can not be chambared with lethal munition on Green alert.
- CCO is to pioritize safety of Command members in acordance to Chain of Command, with piority given to NTR
- CCO is allowed to preform arrests if no Command member is in danger, however they must follow security SOP when doing so.
- CCO is permited to use lathal force when defening self, Command member or Crew from clear and present danger however is advised to warn the attacker of it if situation enables it.